questSteps.stepDescription: Talk to Baba Yaga on Lunar Isle about the man in the bed. (Chat 1•✓•1•1•1)
itemsNeeded: Food for all parts of the quest

questSteps.stepDescription: Talk to Baba Yaga again to go to the Dream World. (Chat 1•1•1•1)
Listen Silas. (Chat 1)
Search the bookcase to get a prophecy tablet.
Climb the stairs.
Eavesdrop-on Silas and continue through the tunnel. (Chat 1)
Go through the tunnel then talk to Silas. (Chat 1)
Read Our lives. (Chat 1)
additionalStepInformation: Prepare to face multiple (4-7) Dagannoth at a time. This will go on for a few minutes.
Do not use your dwarf multicannon in this area or you will lose it.

questSteps.stepDescription: Talk to Baba Yaga to be teleported to Rellekka. (Chat 1•1•2)
additionalStepInformation: Prepare to face many Dagannoth.

questSteps.stepDescription: After killing a sufficient amount of Dagannoths, Brundt the Chieftain will command you to get onto his boat.
Talk to Queen Sigrid. (Chat 1•1)
Talk to Brundt to get another seal of passage. (Chat 2)
Talk to Jarvald (on the western pier) and select the option Travel-Waterbirth to head to Waterbirth Island.
additionalStepInformation: Bank before teleporting to Waterbirth. Bring prayer potions and a full load of food. Leave 1 space empty.

questSteps.stepDescription: Talk to Bardur near the cave entrance for a rope. (Chat 1•1)
Make your way to the southwestern tip of the island and tie the rope on the hole then climb down the hole.
Talk to King Vargas. (Chat 1•1•1•1)
Walk King Vargas down the path taking all aggro from vargas to you to reduce attempts. Read Additional info for direct pathing.
additionalStepInformation: Head East and Climb down the ladder.
continuing to the south and then all the way East to the ladder and climb up.
Head West and Climb up the ladder.
Head East and Climb up the Ladder.
Head North-East and Climb up the ladder.

questSteps.stepDescription: Talk to King Vargas. (Chat 1•1)
Talk to Eir. (Chat 1•1•1•1)
Talk to Nial Swiftfling. (Chat 1•1•1)
Talk to Asleif Hamalsdotter. (Chat 1•1•1)
Talk to Eir. (Chat 1)
Speak to Brundt the Chieftain. (Chat 2)
additionalStepInformation: If the spiritual realm sequence is interrupted, speak with Brundt in the long hall in Rellekka to obtain a letter. Read the letter to return.

questSteps.stepDescription: Talk to King Vargas. (Chat 1•1•2•~•~•~•~•~•2)
Talk to Princess Astrid or Prince Brand. (Chat ~)
Talk to Brundt to continue and bank. (Chat 2)
Talk to Brundt in the long hall in Rellekka when you are ready. (Chat 2•1)
itemsRecommended: Combat Equipment for all three styles.

questSteps.stepDescription: Talk to Baba Yaga on the boat. (Chat 1•2•1•1•1)
Climb down the hole on the southwestern tip of the island.
Enter the southern tunnel. (Chat 1)
Enter the next tunnel to fight the Dagannoth sentinels. (Chat 1)
additionalStepInformation: Alternate attacks between the dagannoth, keeping their health within approximately 500 life points to prevent them from healing each other.
High level players with good equipment can just kill one then the other, it is easy to deal more damage than the amount that they are healed.

After defeating the sentinels, you can go to bank to get more food. You don't need to fight the sentinels again. Also you don't need the tablets or the seal of passage for the fights (saves you a few slots for food).

questSteps.stepDescription: Follow the path provided in the quest image. Steps to go through this area in Additional Info.
additionalStepInformation: Head South then East then South. Climb over wall.
Head South click Enter Tunnel Entrance when you see it.
You will be pathed in a counter clockwise circle to the Tunnel Entrance.
Head South until you reach the next Tunnel Entrance.

questSteps.stepDescription: Go through the next tunnel and talk to Dagannoth Mother. (Chat ~)
Start the battle with Balmung (the special weapon you received from Brundt) and kill the Dagannoth Mother, switching styles according to her colour.
additionalStepInformation: Read the following to know what to use when the Dagannoth Mother changes colors. React with the following color.
The Chatbox will also tell you what color the Dagannoth Mother will be.
White - Air spells, including Smoke spells
Blue - Water spells, including Ice spells
Brown - Earth spells, including Shadow spells
Red - Fire spells, including Blood spells
Orange - Melee attacks with Balmung or any slashing weapon
Green - Ranged attacks (officially weak to thrown)

questSteps.stepDescription: After the Dagannoth Mother has been defeated, go back to the previous room, collect the pickaxe and plank and use them to collapse the pillar.
Talk to Eir. (Chat 1•2•1)
Check the bodies and finish chat. (Chat ~)
Talk with Baba Yaga and Koschei. (Chat 2)
Attempt to climb up the rope. (Chat ~•~)
Speak to Brundt. (Chat 2) Brundt will have additional rewards in Rellekka if you have combat skills over 75.
Quest complete!
